        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ui): show cron job ids and running state",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Show each cron job's existing stable ID in the Control UI cron list and agent cron panel.\n- Surface running state from `state.runningAtMs` as `Running` / `Not running` instead of only showing last-run status.\n- Add focused coverage for both the cron page and agent cron panel.\n\nCloses #67629\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Cron job rows expose the existing job identifier and visible running/not-running state in both the Control UI cron list and the agent cron panel.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on this PR branch (`codex/cron-visible-id-running-67629-20260618`) with repository dependencies available, rendering the changed Control UI views through the repository UI test harness.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts --reporter=verbose\nnode --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the local OpenClaw UI render run showed the changed DOM behavior:\n\n```text\n✓ |ui| ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts > cron view > shows cron job ids and running state in job rows\n✓ |ui| ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts > renderAgents > shows cron job ids and running state in the agent cron panel\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  24 passed (24)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 1.32s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The rendered cron view includes `ID: job-running`, `Running`, `ID: job-idle`, and `Not running`; the rendered agent Cron Jobs panel includes `ID: job-beta` and `Running`. The i18n validation completed cleanly for all 18 locales with `changed=false` / `fallbacks=0`, and `git diff --check` produced no output.\n\nWhat was not tested: Browser screenshot proof was not captured in this environment; the focused UI rendering path above verifies the changed DOM output for the affected views.\n\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nCron job rows did not expose the stable job ID or a clear running/not-running state in the Control UI cron list and agent cron panel. This made it harder to correlate visible rows with configured jobs and current execution state.\n\n## Evidence\nFocused UI tests passed after the change: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/agents.test.ts --reporter=verbose`, plus `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check` and `git diff --check`. The detailed test output in the Real behavior proof section shows the changed DOM assertions for job IDs and running state. Browser screenshot proof was not captured for this PR.\n",
        "branch": "codex/cron-visible-id-running-67629-20260618",
